parameters: \unknown\msgevent[1]\lspi[120]Thank you so much for taking care of those bad guys,\. Lyon!
\unknown\msgevent[1]\lspi[120]Here are some items that might help you out!
\unknown\msgevent[1]\lspi[120]Go stop the bandits!\. You're the town's hope!
\unknown\lspi[120]Those people are way too co-ordinated to be ordinary bandits.
\unknown\lspi[120]I'm not sure I can stand up to them alone.\..\..
\unknown\lspi[120]This nauseating feeling.\..\..\. Wait, I've felt this before.
\unknown\lspi[120]It's the same as ten years ago!
\unknown\lspi[120]No.\..\..\. Why does it have to be now!? Mom,\. dad,\. please.\..\..
\n<Greedy Bandit>You got a pretty face,\. the kind that can easily sell for thousands.
\n<Greedy Bandit>Now hold still, you'll depreciate if you get hurt.
\unknown\lspi[120](Oh no,\. I can't shake that feeling.\.\. There's no way I can deal with him right now. I can't\..\..\.. focus.)
\Lyon\unknownA slave trading bandit,\. huh?\.\. Is looting not enough for you people?
\n<Greedy Bandit>What can I say?\.\. Times are tough and the money's good.
\n<Greedy Bandit>There's no demand for meddling brats,\. so I'll leave you to my friends.
\n<Preaching Bandit>Hey kid,\. the world ain't all sunshine and rainbows OK?
\n<Preaching Bandit>Take your morals and ideals with you\| to the afterlife!
\n<Preaching Bandit>I'll show you how it's done!\.\.
\n<Greedy Bandit>Why are my disciples such fools\..\..\..?
\lyon\unknownLet's hope you wise up and surrender.
\n<Greedy Bandit>Grrrr,  we'll see if you can stand up\..\..\.. to this!\|\^
\lyonGood.\| Now,\. why were you off on your own this late at night?
\unknown\lspi[120]I\..\..\.. ran away from Gerth.\|  There was an attack.\|
\unknown\lspi[120]Really?\| Would you be able to save them? \|I wanted to stay and fight\..\..\.. but-\.\.\.
\lyonYou stay safe!\| I will come back for you once I deal with these damned bandits!
\unknown\lspi[120]All right.\|  But,\.\.\. may I ask for your name before you go?
\unknown\lspi[120]Thank you, Lyon.\| I might not be able to fight right now, but, please take these.
Lyon, upon hearing the terrible news, hurried to Gerth.
When he saw the once bustling farming town burning on
the horizon with dark smoke bellowing, his temper flared.
